---
import ServicePage from '@layouts/ServicePage.astro';
import type { Faq } from '@data/site';

const faqs: Faq[] = [
  {
    question: 'Our place is on the bluff above Center Hill. Can a truck even reach the tank?',
    answer:
      'Steep lake lots are the defining access challenge around Center Hill. Hose length, parking and slope determine what is workable — describe the driveway and where the tank sits relative to it, and a provider can judge feasibility before driving out.',
  },
  {
    question: 'We rent our lake house most summer weekends. How does that affect the septic system?',
    answer:
      'Rental turnover concentrates heavy use into short bursts — many loads of laundry and many showers in a weekend. That pattern fills tanks faster than the occupancy count suggests and stresses drain fields. Describe the rental pattern in the request.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does coverage include the communities around the lake, not just Smithville?',
    answer:
      'Requests from Silver Point, Dowelltown, Liberty, Alexandria and the lake communities are reviewed against providers whose range covers DeKalb County. Coverage varies by provider; exact locations get faster availability answers.',
  },
  {
    question: 'We are buying a house outside Smithville. Should the septic be inspected first?',
    answer:
      'A septic inspection before purchase is how buyers learn the condition of a system nobody has documentation for. Whether one is required depends on the transaction — but requesting one is straightforward, and the form has an option for real-estate involvement.',
  },
];
---

<ServicePage
  title="Septic Services in Smithville, TN"
  description="Request septic pumping, repair, inspections and installation in Smithville and DeKalb County, TN — including Center Hill Lake properties and rural homes."
  h1="Septic Services in Smithville and DeKalb County"
  breadcrumbLabel="Septic Services — Smithville"
  serviceName="Septic Services"
  areaServed="Smithville and DeKalb County, Tennessee"
  intro="DeKalb County pairs small-town streets with steep Center Hill Lake country, and nearly all of it runs on septic. Request pumping, repair, inspection or installation for Smithville-area property and describe the site so coverage can be checked."
  faqs={faqs}
  formHeading="Request Service in Smithville"
  related={[
    { label: 'Septic Inspections in Cookeville', href: '/septic-inspection-cookeville-tn/', blurb: 'inspection scopes for purchases and maintenance' },
    { label: 'Emergency Septic Service in Cookeville', href: '/emergency-septic-service-cookeville-tn/', blurb: 'urgent backups and precautions' },
    { label: 'Upper Cumberland Service Area', href: '/service-area/' },
  ]}
>
  <h2>Septic Service in DeKalb County</h2>
  <p>
    Smithville anchors a county shaped by Center Hill Lake. In town, homes are modest and
    established; outside it, the land breaks toward the lake in ridges and hollows dotted with
    weekend houses, retirement builds and short-term rentals. Rural homes and farms fill the
    flatter country toward Dowelltown, Liberty and Alexandria. Different properties, one common
    denominator: private septic systems, many of them decades old and lightly documented.
  </p>

  <h2>Services Available to Request</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Septic pumping and cleaning</strong> — routine service, overdue tanks, pre-listing preparation</li>
    <li><strong>Repair evaluation</strong> — backups, alarms, suspected leaks and distribution problems</li>
    <li><strong>Inspections</strong> — lake-house purchases and maintenance checks; see <a href="/septic-inspection-cookeville-tn/">how inspection scopes differ</a></li>
    <li><strong>Installation and replacement</strong> — new builds on family land and failed-system replacements</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Center Hill Factor</h2>
  <p>
    Lake properties concentrate three challenges at once. Access: steep drives and limited
    parking make truck positioning genuinely difficult on some lots. Load: rental weekends push
    brief, intense water use through systems sized for quieter lives. Terrain: slopes constrain
    where drain fields can sit and how they behave in wet seasons. None of this makes service
    impossible — it makes accurate property description essential. A request that says “tank is
    forty feet below the parking pad” gets a realistic answer instead of a surprised provider.
  </p>

  <h2>Common Smithville-Area Requests</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>A lake house purchased sight-unseen on the septic side — locating, pumping and inspection bundled into one visit where possible</li>
    <li>A rental cabin backing up on a holiday weekend — see <a href="/emergency-septic-service-cookeville-tn/">urgent request guidance</a></li>
    <li>A farmhouse tank overdue by a decade, with lids somewhere under the yard</li>
    <li>A new build on subdivided family land needing a full system</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Coverage Notes</h2>
  <p>
    DeKalb County requests are matched against providers whose range and schedule fit; coverage
    varies by provider, service type and location within the county. Availability is not
    guaranteed. The <a href="/service-area/">service area page</a> shows the wider regional
    picture.
  </p>
</ServicePage>
